article.headline: DePaul 69, Bowling Green 59
article.story: ROSEMONT, Ill. (AP) -- Sammy Mejia scored a career-high 22 points and Marlon Brumfield had a career-best 15 rebounds Saturday as DePaul defeated Bowling Green 69-59 in the season opener for both schools. The Blue Demons' Drake Diener scored all 14 of his points in the second half as DePaul rallied from a 25-23 halftime deficit by shooting 57 percent in the final 20 minutes. Josh Almanson and Steven Wright scored 17 points each for the Falcons. Bowling Green led the entire first half when DePaul had 10 turnovers, but the Blue Demons improved their ball handling in the second half with just four turnovers. Diener tied the game with his first basket on the Blue Demons' first possession in the second half and after trading baskets, DePaul took off and built an 11-point lead. Mejia's previous best was 18 points. Brumfield, who added 10 points, eclipsed his career high of six rebounds with eight in the first half.
